{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"ovenproof baking dish, aluminium foil, silicone bread mat, round cookie cutter (5 cm), pastry brush, oven","id":"r126431","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-RXwagNBMp2Y\/XZWfK19p-xI\/AAAAAAAAe_4\/HFfGOcFWozoSEtXVmjmkFKXnRedIs6nkQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_q7C5W1LDghlU7LBH.png","title":"Plum and raspberry cobbler","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"700 g plums, stones removed and flesh cut into 6 wedges"},{"content":"300 g raspberries (fresh or frozen)"},{"content":"1 ½ tbsp brown sugar (see Tips)"},{"content":"2 tbsp orange juice"},{"content":"110 g self-raising flour, plus extra for dusting"},{"content":"80 g wholemeal spelt flour (see Tips)"},{"content":"1 tsp baking powder"},{"content":"90 g butter, chilled and cut into pieces (2-3 cm)"},{"content":"1 tsp ground cinnamon"},{"content":"2 eggs"},{"content":"milk, for brushing"},{"content":"pouring (whipping) cream, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"4.8 g","fat":"5.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"24.6 g","calories":"729 kJ \/ 173 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 160°C."},{"content":"Place an ovenproof baking dish (approx. 22 cm) onto mixing bowl lid and weigh plums and raspberries into it. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of the brown sugar over fruit and toss lightly to coat."},{"content":"Drizzle orange juice over fruit, cover with aluminium foil and bake for 15 minutes (160°C). Remove foil and bake for a further 10-15 minutes (160°C), or until fruit is almost tender."},{"content":"Place flours, baking powder, butter, cinnamon and remaining 1 tablespoon sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add eggs and knead <b>10-12 sec\/<b>, until just combined."},{"content":"Transfer mixture onto a lightly floured silicone bread mat or work surface. Gently shape into a ball, then press into a flat disc (approx. 2 cm thickness). Using a round cookie cutter (5 cm), cut out rounds from dough. Re-roll pastry off cuts and cut out remaining rounds (approx. 11 rounds total)."},{"content":"Arrange rounds on top of fruit, pressing down gently, and brush with a little milk. Bake for 30-35 minutes (160°C), or until golden and cooked through. Drizzle with cream (optional) and serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can use your preferred brown sugar in this recipe – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar.","If you don’t have wholemeal spelt flour on hand, you can use wholemeal plain flour instead."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 25m","8 portions"]}